Steps install Pentaho

1 - Download http://sourceforge.net/projects/pentaho/

2 - Unzip download.

3 - Execute sudo ./spoon.sh

Steps create repository using Mysql

1 - Download mysql server
  # apt-get install mysql-server
2 - Download mysql client
  # apt-get install mysql-client
3 - Download lib mysql for java
  # apt-get install libmysql-java
4 - Download jdbc-mysql coneector
  Download in Platform Independent (mysql-connector-java-5.1.29.tar.gz) http://dev.mysql.com/downloads/connector/j/
5 - Copy las download for /data-integration/lib/
